# O.cap.sdd

Scope: Latin uppercase O prototype glyph.

## Must

- Establish uppercase round-form overshoot.
- Establish relationship between outer curve and counter.
- Test contrast logic against H.
- Make sidebearings visibly compatible with H without flattening the roundness.

## Must not

- Become a perfect geometric oval unless that is later chosen as the design direction.
- Hide optical correction decisions.

## Owns

- Uppercase round-form logic.
- Round overshoot proposal.
- Counter shape proposal for uppercase rounds.

## Depends on

- `H.cap.sdd`
- `../../design-principles.sdd`
- `../../metrics/spacing.sdd`

## Forbids

- Round sidebearings copied mechanically from straight glyphs.

## Done when

- O works in `OOO`, `HOH`, `OHO`, and mixed uppercase/lowercase proof strings.
- Human review accepts its roundness, counter tension, and overshoot behavior.

## Proof-Control Note

- This spec is retained as a legacy proof control for SpecDD system integrity.
- Primary design-DNA for Phase 1 is now `adhesion` (`a d h e s i o n`).
- `H/O/n/o/a` remain as cross-project controls while Phase 1 builds new `adhesion` control glyphs.